This paper is about dialogue generation using deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The paper also involves training a neural network using policy gradient methods, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using human judges, which could be considered a form of user studies (cs.SD).
